# PR Rules

Use these rules to standardize PRs and trigger automatic description generation when requested.

## Response format (required)
- The PR text returned in chat must be wrapped in a ```markdown code block to enable the copy button.
- Always respond with the template inside the code block, ready to copy/paste into the PR description.
- Do not include extra commentary outside the code block; provide only the PR description content inside.
- Ensure headings, lists, and code fences render properly inside the markdown block.
- The response must begin with ```markdown, then `## 📋 Description` on the next line, and end with ```.
- The response must not contain any preface text or blockquotes outside the code block.
- The response must not include any trailing commentary after the closing ```.

## When to auto-generate PR text
If a user asks for a "PR text" (e.g., "PR text", "pull request description", "PR description", "PR template"), generate the description using the template below. The user may ask for this PR text or description in english, portuguese or spanish.

## Triggers (keywords)
- "PR text", "pull request text", "PR description", "PR template"
- "pull request description", "create PR", "text for pull request"
- "texto de PR", "texto para PR", "descrição de PR", "texto para meu PR"
- "pull request description", "criar PR", "texto para pull request"

### PR Shortcut Command
- `!pr` or any case variation (`!PR`, `!pr text`, `!pr description`)
- When user types any variation of `!pr`, immediately trigger the complete PR analysis and generation process

### Optional Mermaid diagram trigger (explicit only)
- Include a simplified Mermaid diagram ONLY if the user explicitly asks for it.
- Trigger keywords (any language): "include mermaid", "add mermaid diagram", "com diagrama mermaid", "diagrama mermaid", "incluir diagrama mermaid".

### Default branches behavior
- If the user does not specify source/target branches, assume:
  - Source: current checked-out branch
  - Target: `develop`
- Use these defaults for title/type detection, diff context, and compliance checks.

## PR title structure
```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

Examples:
- feature(feature): add Tiger token validation middleware
- hotfix(hotfix): resolve role assignment validation error
- migration(migration): initialize grants schema
```

## Description template (use when generating PRs)
The following template must be emitted as raw Markdown (no surrounding code fences):

## 📋 Description
Brief summary of changes made and problem solved.

## 🎯 Motivation and Context
- Why is this change required?
- What problem does it solve?
- Related issue links (if applicable)

## 🔍 PR Analysis & Standards Compliance
Last Commit: <commit_sha>  <!-- fill with `git rev-parse --short HEAD` -->
Standards Reviewed: [project-standards.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project-standards.mdc) | [godoc-english-only.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/godoc-english-only.mdc)

### Compliance Summary
- Overall: [Compliant | Non-compliant]
- GoDoc Language: [Compliant | Non-compliant] - All GoDoc documentation in English
- Notes: [brief notes]

### Non-compliance Findings
- File: path/to/file.go:123
  - Issue: [describe deviation]
  - Standard: [section/topic]
  - Reference: [project-standards.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project-standards.mdc) | [godoc-english-only.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/godoc-english-only.mdc)
