## Generation Process
1. Analyze workspace changes
2. Detect change type from branch prefix (feature/ | hotfix/ | migration/)
3. Resolve PR title scope from branch prefix (feature → feature, hotfix → hotfix, migration → migration)
   - File path scopes remain for body context only (not used in title)
4. Generate content using the template below
5. Validate branch constraints:
   - feature/* and hotfix/*: no constraint beyond general code changes
   - migration/*: changes must be limited to `migrations/`
   - If migration/* includes files outside `migrations/`, mark Non-compliant in the PR template Compliance Summary

## Output Constraints (strict)
- Wrap the entire PR description in a ```markdown code block to enable the copy button in chat.
- Do NOT add any preface or follow-up commentary outside the code block.
- Inside the code block, start with `## 📋 Description` and follow the template exactly.
- Use the template verbatim and fill dynamic fields.
- Do NOT include any meta text like "Here is your PR" or similar before or after the code block.
- The response format should be: ```markdown\n[PR template content]\n```

