## Checklist Heuristics (Type of Change)
Note: These heuristics only help tick the "Type of Change" checklist in the PR body.
They do NOT set the PR title type, which always comes from the branch prefix: feature/ | hotfix/ | migration/.

- If only test files changed → tick "Test improvements"
- If only documentation changed → tick "Documentation update"
- If performance-sensitive diffs detected → tick "Performance improvement"
- If structural renames/reorg without behavior change → tick "Refactoring (no functional changes)"
- If clear bug-fix patterns present → tick "Bug fix"
- Otherwise, if branch is feature/* and adds functionality → tick "New feature"

## Business and Technical Context Integration
- If `domain/` changes → emphasize business rules and entity validation
- If `handlers/` changes → mention permission assignment and sync workflows
- If `repository/` changes → mention data persistence and Spanner operations
- If `usecases/` changes → mention business logic and orchestration
- If `locker/` changes → mention distributed locking and concurrency
- If migrations present → include migration instructions
- If new endpoints → mention API changes
- If tests changed → emphasize coverage improvements
- If config changed → highlight deployment requirements
